    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Moreover, because I have set my affection to the house of my God,.... Had a good will to it, and was earnestly desirous of having it built, and that in a grand manner: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I have of my own proper good; which he had treasured up for his own use: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "of gold and silver, even that I have given to the house of my God; to build or ornament it, or make vessels for it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "over and above all that I have prepared for the holy house; for the building of the temple, which is made mention of in the preceding chapter. ",
